    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1249"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1249">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/575.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Bevan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 8, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With further reference to my despatch number 1263
                    of February 21, I have the honor to transmit herewith a copy of a decree and its
                    English translation<note n="72" xml:id="d1249fn72">Not printed.</note> issued by
                    Governor Luis Caballero on the first day of March, again extending the time for
                    the presentation of manifests of property located in the State of
                    Tamaulipas.</p>
                <p>This decree postpones until the first of May any action that could be taken by
                    the Carrancista officials relative to the expropriation of <pb facs="1003"
                        n="887" xml:id="pg_887"/> foreign property, and gives the property owners
                    ample time to make their manifestations.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thomas H. Bevan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
